# Minimal personal dotfiles.

## Files of interest:

- `profile/bashrc`
- `profile/zshrc`
- `profile/gitconfig`
- `profile/tmux.conf`
- `config/nvim/init.lua`

## Setup

1. Clone the repo to `~/.dotfiles`
2. Symlink the files you want into `$HOME`
3. Put machine- or work-specific environment variables in either:
   - `inc/envs.local`
   - `~/.config/shell/envs.local`

Example:

```bash
git clone git@github.com:metaphox/dotfiles.git ~/.dotfiles
cd .dotfiles
./install.sh
# or
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/zshrc ~/.zshrc
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/gitconfig ~/.gitconfig
ln -s ~/dotfiles/profile/tmux.conf ~/.tmux.conf
```


